-- University of Pennsylvania Gets $15 Million From Baker for Retail Research
-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 2010-10-28T18:13:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/university-of-pennsylvania-gets-15-million-from-baker-for-retail-research.html
The University of Pennsylvania said
Jay Baker, former president of Kohl’s Corp. gave $15 million to
be used to support the Jay H. Baker Retailing Initiative, a
retail industry research center at the university’s Wharton
School.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  